---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "ILVE Appliance Repair Los Angeles | Majestic Range & Brass Burner Specialists";
const description = "Expert ILVE appliance repair in Los Angeles. Majestic, Professional & Nostalgie series — handcrafted near Venice since 1975. Brass burner service, thermocouple, electronic programmer, copper/bronze trim protocol. Same-day service. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — ILVE Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-ilve-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "ILVE Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"ILVE Majestic Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"ILVE Brass Burner Service"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"ILVE Thermocouple Replacement"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"ILVE Professional Series Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"ILVE Electronic Programmer Service"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"ILVE Rotisserie Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does ILVE appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most ILVE repairs run $185–$580. Thermocouple replacement, igniter service, temperature sensor, or electronic programmer reset is on the lower end. Rotisserie motor, gas valve, or control board replacement runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Where are ILVE appliances made?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "ILVE appliances are handcrafted near Venice, Italy — in the Veneto region where the brand has been manufacturing since 1975. Every ILVE Majestic and Professional series range is individually assembled by skilled artisans at the Veneto facility. The proximity to Venice gives ILVE its cultural context: the same attention to craft and material quality that characterizes Venetian artisan traditions."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does my ILVE burner light and then go out?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Thermocouple failure — the most common ILVE service call in Los Angeles. The thermocouple is a safety device that senses the flame and holds the gas valve open. When it degrades, it can't generate enough current to keep the valve open, so the burner ignites but extinguishes 3–30 seconds later. ILVE thermocouples are Italian-spec components at the burner base — we carry OEM ILVE thermocouples for the most common Majestic and Professional configurations."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What makes ILVE's brass burner caps different to service?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "ILVE Majestic ranges use solid brass burner caps — unique in the residential range market where most brands use cast iron or aluminum. Brass caps are softer than cast iron and react differently to cleaning agents: abrasive cleaners scratch the finish, and harsh chemicals oxidize the brass surface. We clean ILVE brass burners using brass-appropriate methods — non-abrasive technique, appropriate brass-safe agents, and dry thoroughly to prevent oxidation. The brass cap geometry also positions the igniter at a specific point relative to the flame path."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you service ILVE's electronic programmer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. ILVE's electronic programmer — the digital clock and timer system that controls oven function scheduling on the Majestic series — is a common service point. Most programmer failures in LA are caused by power fluctuations affecting the Italian electronic module. We diagnose using ILVE's European service documentation and attempt reset procedures before any component replacement. A reset resolves many ILVE programmer failures without parts."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you service all ILVE series including Majestic, Professional, and Nostalgie?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — all ILVE series. The Majestic is ILVE's flagship: brass burner caps, copper or chrome trim, full electronic programmer, optional rotisserie. The Professional series uses the same Italian engineering with a more streamlined aesthetic. The Nostalgie brings a retro-inspired design to the ILVE range philosophy. All three share core component families — thermocouple, gas valve, and sealed system architecture — with series-specific trim and electronics."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .series-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .series-card { background: #161616; padding: 22px 18px; }
  .series-badge { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .series-name { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .series-desc { font-size: 12px; color: #666; line-height: 1.6; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-brass { border-color: #c8820a; background: #fff8f0; }
  .tip-brass .tip-label { color: #c8820a; }
  .tip-italy { border-color: #2a5ea5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-italy .tip-label { color: #2a5ea5; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-brass { background: #c8820a; }
  .tag-programmer { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-trim { background: #5a2a7a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .series-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">ILVE Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        ILVE Repair.<br/>
        <span>Brass Burner. Majestic.</span><br/>
        Near Venice, Italy.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        ILVE has been handcrafting ranges near Venice since 1975. Solid brass burner caps no other residential brand uses. Copper, bronze, and chrome trim that requires specific service care. The thermocouple — the most common ILVE failure in LA — is an Italian-spec safety component we carry on the truck. Same day across LA.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">ILVE Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Brass Burner Cap Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Thermocouple Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Copper / Bronze Trim Protocol</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About ILVE</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Handcrafted Near Venice. Brass Burners. Since 1975.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      ILVE has been manufacturing cooking appliances in the Veneto region of northern Italy — near Venice — since 1975. Every ILVE Majestic and Professional series range is individually assembled by artisan craftspeople at the Veneto facility. The result is a range that carries the fingerprints of its makers in the most literal sense: the brass burner caps are hand-fitted, the copper or chrome trim is hand-applied, and the electronic programmer is calibrated by hand before shipping.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      In Los Angeles, ILVE has found a specific audience: owners who want an Italian cooking range that announces its provenance clearly — through solid brass burner caps that no other brand uses, through the warmth of copper or bronze trim against stainless steel, through the 150cm configuration with eight burners and dual ovens that makes a statement about cooking ambition. These ranges deserve technicians who understand what they're looking at. Not every LA appliance company does.
    </p>

    <div class="series-grid">
      <div class="series-card">
        <div class="series-badge">Flagship</div>
        <div class="series-name">Majestic Series</div>
        <div class="series-desc">ILVE's defining range. Solid brass burner caps. Copper, chrome, or bronze trim. Electronic programmer with clock timer. Optional rotisserie and warming drawer. Available 90cm through 150cm. The range that established ILVE's reputation worldwide.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="series-card">
        <div class="series-badge">Professional</div>
        <div class="series-name">Professional Series</div>
        <div class="series-desc">Commercial-inspired aesthetic with ILVE's Italian engineering. Streamlined design with the same sealed burner performance and multifunction electric oven cavity as the Majestic. Available in multiple configurations and finishes.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="series-card">
        <div class="series-badge">Retro-Inspired</div>
        <div class="series-name">Nostalgie Series</div>
        <div class="series-desc">ILVE's retro-inspired line — vintage aesthetic with modern Italian engineering. Rounded edges, cream and pastel color options, antique brass trim. Popular in LA's design-conscious kitchens alongside Smeg for a coordinated vintage-Italian palette.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-brass" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🔶 Brass Burner Caps — Why They Require Different Service</div>
      <div class="tip-text">ILVE Majestic ranges use solid brass burner caps — a material choice unique in the residential range market. Cast iron (BlueStar, FiveStar, Wolf) and aluminum (most European sealed burners) are the standard. Brass is softer than cast iron and more reactive than aluminum, which means specific service considerations: abrasive cleaning scratches the brass surface and removes its finish; acidic cleaning agents (like vinegar-based degreasers common in general appliance service) cause brass oxidation that turns the cap surface dark brown. We clean ILVE brass burner caps using brass-appropriate technique — soft non-abrasive agents, immediate drying after cleaning, and visual inspection of the igniter tip position relative to the brass cap geometry before reassembly.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every ILVE Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All ILVE series — Majestic, Professional, Nostalgie — across all configurations 90cm to 150cm. Same-day across Los Angeles County.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Majestic Range Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">ILVE Majestic ranges — 90cm, 100cm, 120cm, and 150cm configurations with five to eight sealed gas burners, multifunction electric or dual-fuel oven, and signature brass burner caps. The thermocouple is the most frequent Majestic failure: the burner lights and then extinguishes 3–30 seconds later. We carry OEM ILVE thermocouples for the Majestic's burner configurations on the truck. Brass burner cap service follows brass-appropriate protocol throughout every Majestic call.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: thermocouple failure (most common) · brass burner cap service · igniter failure · gas valve · oven temperature sensor · convection fan · electronic programmer · door gasket · triple-glazed door hinge</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">📟</div>
        <div class="service-name">Electronic Programmer Service</div>
        <div class="service-desc">ILVE Majestic's electronic programmer — the digital clock and timer module that controls oven scheduling, delayed start, and cook duration on the range's control panel — is a distinctive ILVE feature that has no equivalent on most other residential ranges. The programmer uses Italian-sourced electronics that respond to LA's variable power quality differently than the stable European grid voltage it was calibrated for. Power fluctuation-induced programmer faults often resolve with reset procedures without parts. We attempt resets before any programmer replacement.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: programmer not responding · clock reset fault · timer not activating oven · display failure · power fluctuation damage · reset procedures · OEM programmer replacement (Italian sourcing)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔩</div>
        <div class="service-name">Thermocouple Service</div>
        <div class="service-desc">ILVE's Italian-spec thermocouples are the most common ILVE service call in Los Angeles — and the most important to get right. The thermocouple generates a small electrical current when heated by the burner flame; this current holds the safety gas valve open. As it degrades, the current drops below the threshold needed to keep the valve open. We test thermocouple output current before replacing — confirming degradation rather than replacing prematurely. Thermocouple geometry and mounting position are burner-cap-specific on ILVE Majestic configurations.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Thermocouple output testing · OEM ILVE thermocouple replacement · safety valve assessment · burner-specific geometry · post-replacement flame stability verification</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍗</div>
        <div class="service-name">Rotisserie &amp; Warming Drawer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">The ILVE Majestic rotisserie — an optional feature on larger Majestic configurations — uses a dedicated motor that drives the spit rod at low speed through the oven cavity. Rotisserie motor failure is a distinct service from the oven heating or fan systems. The warming drawer beneath the main oven cavity also has its own heating element and thermostat. We service both the rotisserie motor assembly and the warming drawer system as independent subsystems.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: rotisserie motor failure · spit rod engagement · rotisserie control circuit · warming drawer element · warming drawer thermostat · temperature calibration</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">✨</div>
        <div class="service-name">Copper / Bronze / Chrome Trim Service</div>
        <div class="service-desc">ILVE's distinctive metal trim options — polished copper, antique bronze, satin nickel, and chrome — are applied to the control panel frame, oven door frame, handle hardware, and knob surrounds. Each metal finish requires specific cleaning chemistry during service: copper and bronze oxidize with acid-based cleaners; chrome scratches with abrasive compounds. We apply metal-appropriate cleaning agents and protective covers to all trim surfaces during every ILVE Majestic service call.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">All repairs with trim-appropriate protocols — copper and bronze safe cleaning agents, non-abrasive chrome technique, protective covers throughout, and finish verification before and after service.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Oven Temperature &amp; Convection Service</div>
