<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">ILVE Engineering — What Sets It Apart to Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">ILVE's Venetian artisan manufacturing creates specific components and design choices that require knowledge beyond generic Italian range experience.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Solid Brass Burner Caps</strong> — No other residential range uses solid brass burner caps. Brass conducts heat differently than cast iron, positioning the igniter spark point at a geometry specific to the ILVE Majestic design. Brass also requires specific cleaning: abrasive agents scratch, acids oxidize. After decades of cast iron service, a general technician's cleaning instinct is wrong for ILVE brass. We adapt cleaning protocol to brass on every Majestic call.</li>
        <li><strong>Italian Thermocouple System</strong> — ILVE's burner safety uses an Italian-spec thermocouple-to-valve circuit with specific millivolt output requirements. The thermocouple generates approximately 6–12 millivolts when functioning correctly; the safety valve requires a minimum of 5 millivolts to stay open. As the thermocouple ages, output drops gradually — the burner stays lit for shorter periods before extinguishing. Testing millivolt output tells us exactly how degraded the thermocouple is before we replace it.</li>
        <li><strong>Multifunction Electric Oven (8 Functions)</strong> — ILVE's multifunction oven offers eight distinct cooking modes — each with specific combinations of upper element, lower element, grill, and fan activation. This is more complex than the typical 3–5 function oven. A failure in one element affects multiple functions simultaneously. We map the fault to the specific element by testing which functions fail and which succeed before ordering any parts.</li>
        <li><strong>Triple-Glazed Door System</strong> — ILVE Majestic's oven door uses three panes of glass for maximum insulation. This creates a heavier door than standard double-glazed designs — typically 8–12 kg of door weight that the hinge mechanism must support. ILVE's hinge system is designed for this load, but over years of use the spring tension degrades and the door begins to fall open rather than staying in position. We check door hinge tension on every ILVE oven call.</li>
        <li><strong>Electronic Programmer with Clock</strong> — ILVE Majestic's control panel includes a multi-function programmer that allows oven scheduling, delayed start, and automatic shutoff. The programmer uses Italian electronic components calibrated for 220V European power at consistent quality. LA's 240V residential supply with its occasional fluctuations affects the programmer differently than European stable power. Many ILVE programmer "failures" in LA are recoverable through reset sequences without parts replacement.</li>
        <li><strong>Custom Color and Trim Combinations</strong> — ILVE Majestic can be ordered in a wide range of body colors (similar to Smeg and Bertazzoni's approach) with copper, bronze, satin nickel, or chrome trim. Each trim metal requires specific cleaning chemistry. We identify the trim metal before any cleaning agent contact and apply metal-appropriate protocols throughout the service visit.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#c8820a; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#e8a030">🔥 The 150cm ILVE — Service Considerations</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">ILVE's 150cm Majestic configuration is the largest range the brand produces — eight sealed gas burners across a 60-inch cooktop width, dual independent oven cavities, full electronic programmer for both ovens, and optional warming drawer. Service on the 150cm requires knowing which oven cavity is affected before any diagnosis (left and right cavities have independent temperature sensors, control circuits, and heating elements). When both cavities show simultaneous temperature issues on the 150cm, we check the shared programmer and main control board before individual cavity diagnosis — the same sequential approach we use on the FiveStar 60-inch dual oven.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a150f; border-color:#2a7a2a; margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#5abf5a">🏡 ILVE in LA — Where These Ranges Live</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">ILVE has found a specific LA audience: Bel Air and Beverly Hills custom kitchens where the copper-trim Majestic is specified by a designer as the centerpiece. Malibu estate kitchens where the 150cm configuration dominates an oversized kitchen. West Hollywood and Silver Lake renovation kitchens where the Nostalgie's vintage Italian aesthetic aligns with the home's direction. These ranges are present in fewer LA kitchens than Bertazzoni or Viking — which means the owner almost certainly chose ILVE deliberately, for specific reasons, and knows exactly what they have. Service should match that knowledge.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
