    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common ILVE Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Burner Lights Then Goes Out</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Thermocouple degradation — the most common ILVE service call in LA. The burner ignites normally but extinguishes 3–30 seconds after releasing the knob. We test thermocouple millivolt output to confirm degradation (output below the 5mV threshold) before replacing. OEM ILVE thermocouples on the truck — most of these calls resolve same day.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">📟 Electronic Programmer Not Responding</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">LA power fluctuation-induced programmer fault — the Italian electronic module entered protection or error mode. Many ILVE programmer failures recover fully through reset sequences. We attempt reset procedures using ILVE European documentation before any programmer replacement. Reset resolves a significant percentage of ILVE programmer calls — saving the owner from a 2–4 week Italian sourcing wait.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-programmer">Programmer</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔶 Brass Burner Cap Oxidation</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Cleaning with incorrect agents — acid-based degreasers (vinegar, citrus-based cleaners common in LA households) oxidize brass and turn the caps dark brown. General appliance technicians unfamiliar with ILVE often use inappropriate cleaning chemistry. We can slow oxidation with brass-appropriate treatment. Severely oxidized caps may require replacement with OEM ILVE brass caps.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-brass">Brass Burner</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🚪 Triple-Glazed Door Falling Open</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Door hinge spring tension loss from sustained support of the triple-glazed door's weight. The door no longer stays in position — it falls to horizontal rather than holding at the owner's chosen angle. ILVE hinge spring replacement restores the holding tension. We check door hinge tension on every ILVE oven call, noting when it's beginning to weaken before it progresses to full tension loss.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🎨 Metal Trim Damage from Service</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Owners calling after a previous service left marks on their copper or bronze trim — this is a legitimate concern and we hear it regularly. Acid cleaners oxidize copper and bronze; abrasive tools scratch chrome. Once damaged, metal trim requires specialist refinishing. We apply metal-appropriate protocols and protective covers on every ILVE call, and confirm trim condition before and after service.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-trim">Trim Finish</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Temperature Inconsistency</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Temperature sensor drift or multifunction selector fault. ILVE ovens use Italian-spec sensors that can drift from calibration over time. We test with a calibrated probe at multiple setpoints and attempt calibration adjustment before ordering any sensor. The multifunction selector on ILVE Majestic controls element combinations for each of the eight cooking modes — a selector fault affects specific modes while leaving others functional.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
