<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">09 — FAQ</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">ILVE Repair FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Why does my ILVE burner light and then go out?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Thermocouple degradation — the most common ILVE failure in LA. The thermocouple generates a small electrical current that holds the safety gas valve open while the burner is lit. When it degrades, the current drops below the threshold and the valve closes, extinguishing the flame. We test thermocouple millivolt output before replacing. OEM ILVE thermocouples are typically on the truck — most thermocouple calls are same-day repairs.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What makes ILVE's brass burner caps different from other ranges?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">ILVE Majestic uses solid brass burner caps — no other residential range does this. Brass requires specific cleaning: acid-based degreasers (including vinegar and citrus cleaners) oxidize brass and turn it dark brown. Abrasive cleaners scratch the brass surface. We use brass-appropriate cleaning agents only and apply protective covers during all ILVE service work. Oxidized brass can often be restored with professional brass treatment — but severely oxidized caps require OEM replacement.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">My ILVE electronic programmer went blank after a power surge — is it broken?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Often recoverable. LA's power fluctuations affect ILVE's Italian electronic programmer differently than the stable European grid voltage it was designed for. Many programmer faults after power events are protection mode shutdowns that respond to specific reset sequences from ILVE's European service documentation. We attempt resets before any programmer replacement — a reset resolves a significant portion of programmer calls without parts.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can you service the 150cm ILVE Majestic with dual ovens?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — including all eight burners, the integrated griddle if present, and both independent oven cavities. Single cavity failures are isolated to that cavity's independent circuit. Simultaneous dual-cavity issues are diagnosed at the shared programmer and control board before individual cavity component diagnosis — preventing unnecessary double-component replacement.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How long does it take to get ILVE parts?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">For common components — thermocouples, igniters, temperature sensors, door gaskets — ILVE US distribution typically provides 1–3 business day delivery. For less common parts — electronic programmer, rotisserie motor, specialty trim hardware — Italian sourcing adds 2–4 weeks. We check US stock before quoting timelines and tell you honestly when Italian sourcing is needed before beginning work.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you service all ILVE series — Majestic, Professional, and Nostalgie?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — all three series. The Majestic is ILVE's flagship with brass caps, metal trim, and electronic programmer. The Professional uses the same Italian engineering with a more streamlined design. The Nostalgie brings a retro-inspired aesthetic. All three share core component families — thermocouple, gas valve, heating elements — with series-specific electronics and trim.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
